    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go to the List of Blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <em>Content</em> block to display the contents of a post or page. This block is a child block of the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/query-loop-block/\"><em>Query Loop</em></a> block and helps to customize the appearance of the query loop. <strong>The option to add this block is only available in <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/site-editor/\">Site editor</a>.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a <em>Content</em> block, first ensure that you are editing the page or post template. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"543\" height=\"850\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-list-view.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of the document overview sidebar in the WordPress edit Template screen. The list view tab is active and a content block is highlighted. \" class=\"wp-image-16365624\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-list-view.jpg 543w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-list-view-192x300.jpg 192w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 543px) 100vw, 543px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The list view tab of the document overview</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After block you want to precede Content block, hover to activate the <strong>inline block Inserter</strong> and click to add the <em>Content</em> block in the desired location. You may need to type <em>Content</em> in the block search dialog to find it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"880\" height=\"664\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-inserter.jpg\" alt=\"A screenshot of the inline block inserter. The search bar of the block inserter contains the text &quot;content&quot;. The Content block is available as an option to insert into the page.\" class=\"wp-image-16365626\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-inserter.jpg 880w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-inserter-300x226.jpg 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-inserter-768x579.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 880px) 100vw, 880px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Adding Content block via the inline block inserter</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also type <kbd>/content</kbd> and hit enter in a new paragraph block to add the <em>Content</em> block quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"780\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-slash-inserter.jpg\" alt=\"How to add Content block quickly\" class=\"wp-image-16365625\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-slash-inserter.jpg 940w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-slash-inserter-300x249.jpg 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-slash-inserter-768x637.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Adding Content via &#8220;/&#8221; quick-add</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The inner blocks contain an empty paragraph as a template when the Content block doesn&#8217;t already have content in it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"223\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/268028952-efb999ca-1819-4e93-b942-b60993608e31-1024x223.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of the empty paragraph in inner block when the block doesn't have any other content in it.\" class=\"wp-image-16359941\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/268028952-efb999ca-1819-4e93-b942-b60993608e31-1024x223.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/268028952-efb999ca-1819-4e93-b942-b60993608e31-300x65.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/268028952-efb999ca-1819-4e93-b942-b60993608e31-768x168.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/03/268028952-efb999ca-1819-4e93-b942-b60993608e31.png 1517w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To view the block toolbar, click on the block and the toolbar will be displayed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block comes with unique toolbar icons. These block-specific controls allow you to manipulate the block right in the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Content</em> block shows four buttons in the block toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Drag icon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Move arrows</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"362\" height=\"118\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-23-at-3.08.55-PM.png\" alt=\"Content block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-15489608\" style=\"width:272px;height:89px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-23-at-3.08.55-PM.png 362w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-23-at-3.08.55-PM-300x98.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 362px) 100vw, 362px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Content block toolbar</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Transform to</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the <strong>Transform</strong> button to convert into Columns, Details, Group, or Excerpt blocks.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Excerpt</strong>: Display only a trimmed version of the post content, commonly used in blog listings or archive templates.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Columns</strong>: Organize your content into multiple columns for a more structured layout.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Details</strong>: Collapse content inside a toggle panel to display it on demand.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Group</strong>: Wrap the block in a container, allowing you to apply background, spacing, and layout styles.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"632\" height=\"555\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-transforms.png\" alt=\"The transform dropdown on the Content block\" class=\"wp-image-16365623\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-transforms.png 632w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-transforms-300x263.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 632px) 100vw, 632px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Content block transform options</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Drag icon</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"362\" height=\"118\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/02-post-content.png\" alt=\"Drag icon in the Content block\" class=\"wp-image-15489611\" style=\"width:181px;height:59px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/02-post-content.png 362w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/02-post-content-300x98.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 362px) 100vw, 362px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Content block drag icon</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To drag and drop the block to a new location on the page template, click and hold the <strong>drag</strong> icon, then drag the block to the new location. The blue separator line indicates where the block will be placed. Release the left mouse button when you find the new location to place the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Move arrows</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/01-post-content-1.png\" alt=\"Move arrows in the Content block\" class=\"wp-image-15489612\" style=\"width:181px;height:59px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Move arrows in the Content block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>up and down</strong> arrow icons can be used to move the block up and down on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/moving-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\">Get more information about moving a block within the editor.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Options </strong>button on a block toolbar gives you more features to customize the block.&nbsp;These controls allow you to duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the block toolbar, every block has specific options in the editor sidebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>If you do not see the sidebar, click the <strong>settings </strong>icon next to the <strong>Save </strong>button.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"444\" height=\"78\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-1.png\" alt=\"The block settings icon\" class=\"wp-image-16356772\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-1.png 444w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-1-300x53.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 444px) 100vw, 444px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, the Block Settings panel is divided into <strong>Settings </strong>and <strong>Styles </strong>tabs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Layout </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Layout menu under the Settings tab lets you add custom content width to the <em>Content</em> block.\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you toggle this option off, the <em>Content</em> block inherits the layout width options set by the theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"213\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/content-width-1024x213.png\" alt=\"Content width options\" class=\"wp-image-16356773\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/content-width-1024x213.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/content-width-300x62.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/content-width-768x160.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/content-width-1536x319.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/content-width.png 1891w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Content width inherited from the layout</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Otherwise, you can customize the content width and justification when it&#8217;s toggled on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"220\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-content-width-1024x220.png\" alt=\"Setting content width for Content block\" class=\"wp-image-16356775\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-content-width-1024x220.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-content-width-300x64.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-content-width-768x165.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-content-width-1536x329.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-content-width.png 1693w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Setting the custom Content width</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"422\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/justification-1-1024x422.png\" alt=\"Setting Justification for Content block\" class=\"wp-image-16356776\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/justification-1-1024x422.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/justification-1-300x124.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/justification-1-768x317.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/justification-1-1536x634.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/justification-1.png 1896w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Setting constrained layout justification</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Advanced settings&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Advanced section lets you add CSS class(es) to your block. This will allow you to write custom CSS and styles to the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/ql3NySmHv-UbS9HqLQkycDVcqQgSyKGuS28dVa4ojJeiib3CGQm_XLFCXFS6ma9DEQeizapklRsYYvPbWVAFmaMAlNaYak-IeckP2MrqkRFQQ8ToUjXSR4tshb47jFQPgSLIMy_T\" alt=\"Advanced setting in Content block\" style=\"width:283px;height:151px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Advanced setting in Content block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Styles</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Heading Color\u00a0</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Content block now supports\u00a0<strong>heading color customization</strong>. You can define a default color for headings (e.g., H1\u2013H6) directly within the block settings or through Global Styles. This makes it easier to ensure consistent typography and design across your templates. When applied, block-level heading color styles will take precedence over global settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"972\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-heading-1024x972.png\" alt=\"Heading color settings\" class=\"wp-image-16365622\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-heading-1024x972.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-heading-300x285.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-heading-768x729.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/content-heading.png 1099w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Heading color settings</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Typography</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The under the <strong>Style </strong>tab, you to change the block content\u2019s font size.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"239\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/typography-supports-1-1024x239.png\" alt=\"Typography support for Content block\" class=\"wp-image-16356777\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/typography-supports-1-1024x239.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/typography-supports-1-300x70.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/typography-supports-1-768x179.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/typography-supports-1-1536x358.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/typography-supports-1.png 1910w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Changing font size in the Content block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Get more details about changing typography settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"dimensions\">Dimensions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>paragraph</em> block provides various options to adjust its dimensions, such as width and height, allowing you to customize the text layout to ensure visual consistency.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Dimension settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Border</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>paragraph</em> block provides border settings options to add border color, width, and radius.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/border-settings-overview/\">Border settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update 2025-04-22 (props to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/karthickmurugan/\">@karthickmurugan</a> and <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/milana_cap/\">@milana_cap</a>)\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add Border and Spacing support</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add Heading color support</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update screenshots to 6.8 version</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update title to Content block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update all instances for block name</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update availability of the block (only in Site editor) and content that explains it.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-08-24\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated screenshots for 6.3</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Instructions now account for adding the block as a child block of a Query Loop</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-04-25\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated screenshots for 6.2</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added typography support</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2022-03-25</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
